title: Episode 23: LIVE from the Midwestern Psychological Association Conference
itunes:author: UW-Green Bay Psychology Department
itunes:summary: In this final episode of the season, Allee Schramm and Ryan Martin interview more than 15 students from 7 different universities about the research they presented at the 2016 Midwestern Psychological Association Conference in Chicago. Topics ranged from stereotype threat to autism to communication during sex.
